<subSubSection id="C33E44D6FFBEFFFB809028EB336A977D" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9B175DFFBEFFFB809028EB336A977D" blockId="6.[136,1452,1522,2088]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="B950CB4FFFBEFFFB809028EB367299C9" bold="true" box="[189,356,1666,1692]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">Comments:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C246CDEFFBEFFFB814928EB353499C9" box="[356,546,1666,1692]" class="Myxomycetes" family="Cribrariaceae" genus="Cribraria" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Liceales" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" phylum="Mycetozoa" rank="species" species="lepida">
<emphasis id="B950CB4FFFBEFFFB814928EB353499C9" box="[356,546,1666,1692]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">Cribraria lepida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the closely related species 
<taxonomicName id="4C246CDEFFBEFFFB842D28EB339299C9" authorityName="Rex" authorityYear="1891" box="[1024,1156,1666,1692]" class="Myxomycetes" family="Cribrariaceae" genus="Cribraria" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Liceales" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" phylum="Mycetozoa" rank="species" species="violacea">
<emphasis id="B950CB4FFFBEFFFB842D28EB339299C9" box="[1024,1156,1666,1692]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">C. violacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in size and shape of the calyculus, the structure of the network of threads, and shape of the nodules. The latter has a deep cup-shaped calyculus, taking from 1/2 to 2/3 of the sporotheca, nodules large, flat, angular. Spores of 
<taxonomicName id="4C246CDEFFBEFFFB843628A3338B99B1" authorityName="Rex" authorityYear="1891" box="[1051,1181,1738,1764]" class="Myxomycetes" family="Cribrariaceae" genus="Cribraria" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Liceales" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" phylum="Mycetozoa" rank="species" species="violacea">
<emphasis id="B950CB4FFFBEFFFB843628A3338B99B1" box="[1051,1181,1738,1764]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">C. violacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in transmitted light are lilac, and more brightly coloured than those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C246CDEFFBEFFFB828D2887341E985D" box="[672,776,1774,1800]" class="Myxomycetes" family="Cribrariaceae" genus="Cribraria" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Liceales" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" phylum="Mycetozoa" rank="species" species="lepida">
<emphasis id="B950CB4FFFBEFFFB828D2887341E985D" box="[672,776,1774,1800]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">C. lepida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Examination of samples of 
<taxonomicName id="4C246CDEFFBEFFFB847D288733AE985D" box="[1104,1208,1774,1800]" class="Myxomycetes" family="Cribrariaceae" genus="Cribraria" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Liceales" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" phylum="Mycetozoa" rank="species" species="lepida">
<emphasis id="B950CB4FFFBEFFFB847D288733AE985D" box="[1104,1208,1774,1800]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">C. lepida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C246CDEFFBEFFFB84DC28873264985D" authorityName="Rex" authorityYear="1891" box="[1265,1394,1774,1800]" class="Myxomycetes" family="Cribrariaceae" genus="Cribraria" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Liceales" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" phylum="Mycetozoa" rank="species" species="violacea">
<emphasis id="B950CB4FFFBEFFFB84DC28873264985D" box="[1265,1394,1774,1800]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">C. violacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with a binocular microscope reveals that these species are similar only in colouration of sporocarps and differ greatly in shape and structure of peridium and sporotheca. (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB56AACFFBEFFFB8292295F34849805" author="Ejale, A. U. &amp; Gill, L. S." box="[703,914,1846,1872]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" pagination="250 - 252" refId="ref5594" refString="Ejale, A. U. &amp; Gill, L. S. (1991) Identification of Myxomycetes (Order Liceales) from Bendel state Nigeria II. Korean Journal of Mycology 19 (4): 250 - 252." type="journal article" year="1991">Ejale &amp; Gill 1991</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB56AACFFBEFFFB83B2295F33859804" author="Vlasenko, A. V. &amp; Novozhilov, Y. K. &amp; Shchepin, O. N. &amp; Vlasenko, V. A." box="[927,1171,1846,1873]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" pagination="14 - 23" refId="ref6589" refString="Vlasenko, A. V., Novozhilov, Y. K., Shchepin, O. N. &amp; Vlasenko, V. A. (2016) Hydrochory as certain mode of distribution of myxomycetes along floodlands in South of Western Siberia. Mikologiya I Fitopatologiya 50 (1): 14 - 23." type="journal article" year="2016">
Vlasenko 
<emphasis id="B950CB4FFFBEFFFB843F295E33509805" box="[1042,1094,1846,1872]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C246CDEFFBEFFFB848A295F32069805" box="[1191,1296,1846,1872]" class="Myxomycetes" family="Cribrariaceae" genus="Cribraria" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Liceales" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" phylum="Mycetozoa" rank="species" species="lepida">
<emphasis id="B950CB4FFFBEFFFB848A295F32069805" box="[1191,1296,1846,1872]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">C. lepida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the habit of 
<taxonomicName id="4C246CDEFFBEFFFB808A293336449821" authorityName="Rex" authorityYear="1891" box="[167,338,1882,1908]" class="Myxomycetes" family="Cribrariaceae" genus="Cribraria" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Liceales" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" phylum="Mycetozoa" rank="species" species="languescens">
<emphasis id="B950CB4FFFBEFFFB808A293336449821" box="[167,338,1882,1908]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">C. languescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the colour of 
<taxonomicName id="4C246CDEFFBEFFFB820F293335B59821" authorityName="Rex" authorityYear="1891" box="[546,675,1882,1908]" class="Myxomycetes" family="Cribrariaceae" genus="Cribraria" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Liceales" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" phylum="Mycetozoa" rank="species" species="violacea">
<emphasis id="B950CB4FFFBEFFFB820F293335B59821" box="[546,675,1882,1908]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">C. violacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the spore size is given as 5–6 µm (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB56AACFFBEFFFB844E293332B19821" author="Martin, G. W. &amp; Alexopoulos, C. J." box="[1123,1447,1882,1908]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" refId="ref5986" refString="Martin, G. W. &amp; Alexopoulos, C. J. (1969) The Myxomycetes. University of Iowa Press, Iowa City, 560 pp." type="book" year="1969">Martin &amp; Alexopoulos 1969</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB56AACFFBEFFFB80A52917367798CD" author="Neubert, H. &amp; Nowotny, W. &amp; Baumann, K." box="[136,353,1918,1944]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" refId="ref6056" refString="Neubert, H., Nowotny, W. &amp; Baumann, K. (1993) Die Myxomyceten (Band I). Karlheinz Baumann Verlag Gomaringen." type="book" year="1993">
Neubert 
<emphasis id="B950CB4FFFBEFFFB80C52916360E98CD" box="[232,280,1918,1944]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">et al</emphasis>
. 1993
</bibRefCitation>
). From the red-brown to purple-brown 
<taxonomicName id="4C246CDEFFBEFFFB833E291734AD98CD" authorityName="Rex" authorityYear="1891" box="[787,955,1918,1944]" class="Myxomycetes" family="Cribrariaceae" genus="Cribraria" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Liceales" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" phylum="Mycetozoa" rank="species" species="languescens">
<emphasis id="B950CB4FFFBEFFFB833E291734AD98CD" box="[787,955,1918,1944]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">C. languescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
already distinguishes the colour. 
<taxonomicName id="4C246CDEFFBEFFFB8500291732BA98CD" authorityName="Rex" authorityYear="1891" box="[1325,1452,1918,1944]" class="Myxomycetes" family="Cribrariaceae" genus="Cribraria" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Liceales" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" phylum="Mycetozoa" rank="species" species="violacea">
<emphasis id="B950CB4FFFBEFFFB8500291732BA98CD" box="[1325,1452,1918,1944]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">C. violacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is smaller, usually ovoid, the network nodes are more than 50 µm in diameter, the cup takes up half or more of the sporocarps. 
<taxonomicName id="4C246CDEFFBEFFFB813C29AF369F98B5" authorityName="Berk. &amp; M. A. Curtis" authorityYear="1873" box="[273,393,1990,2016]" class="Myxomycetes" family="Cribrariaceae" genus="Cribraria" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Liceales" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" phylum="Mycetozoa" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis id="B950CB4FFFBEFFFB813C29AF369F98B5" box="[273,393,1990,2016]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">C. elegans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is red-violet, the total height remains below 
<quantity id="4CDCBAB8FFBEFFFB83A129AF34C698B5" box="[908,976,1990,2016]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
, the granulation is coarser (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB56AACFFBEFFFB852029AF37D29751" author="Neubert, H. &amp; Nowotny, W. &amp; Baumann, K." pageId="6" pageNumber="37" refId="ref6056" refString="Neubert, H., Nowotny, W. &amp; Baumann, K. (1993) Die Myxomyceten (Band I). Karlheinz Baumann Verlag Gomaringen." type="book" year="1993">
Neubert 
<emphasis id="B950CB4FFFBEFFFB855F29AE32B398B5" box="[1394,1445,1990,2016]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">et al</emphasis>
. 1993
</bibRefCitation>
). It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C246CDEFFBEFFFB8152298335169751" authorityName="Rex" authorityYear="1891" box="[383,512,2026,2052]" class="Myxomycetes" family="Cribrariaceae" genus="Cribraria" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Liceales" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" phylum="Mycetozoa" rank="species" species="violacea">
<emphasis id="B950CB4FFFBEFFFB8152298335169751" box="[383,512,2026,2052]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">C. violacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in that it has a much shallower calyculus and has numerous thickened nodes, not a few flat nodes on the peridial net (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB56AACFFBEFFFB822A26673438977D" author="Estrada-Torres, A. &amp; Wrigley de Basanta, D. &amp; Conde, E. &amp; Lado, C." box="[519,814,2062,2088]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" pagination="17 - 56" refId="ref5676" refString="Estrada-Torres, A., Wrigley de Basanta, D., Conde, E. &amp; Lado, C. (2009) Myxomycetes associated with dryland ecosystems of the Tehuacan-Cuicatlan Valley Biosphere Reserve, Mexico. Fungal Diversity 36: 17 - 56." type="journal article" year="2009">
Estrada-Torres 
<emphasis id="B950CB4FFFBEFFFB8299266635F0977D" box="[692,742,2062,2088]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">et al</emphasis>
. 2009
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB56AACFFBEFFFB831426673367977D" author="Ramirez-Ortega, J. M. &amp; Estrada-Torres, A. &amp; De Luna, E." box="[825,1137,2062,2088]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" pagination="391 - 419" refId="ref6304" refString="Ramirez-Ortega, J. M., Estrada-Torres, A. &amp; De Luna, E. (2017) A comparative SEM study of morphological characters in Cribraria. Mycotaxon 132: 391 - 419. https: // dx. doi. org / 10.5248 / 132.391" type="journal article" year="2017">
Ramírez-Ortega 
<emphasis id="B950CB4FFFBEFFFB83D82666333B977D" box="[1013,1069,2062,2088]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">et al.</emphasis>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
